# Ground rule: no credentials or connection strings ever committed (see CLAUDE.md, .claude/rules/portability.md)
.env
*.env
**/.env
connections.toml
**/connections.toml
.databrickscfg
**/.databrickscfg
*credentials*
*.pem
*.key
*secret*
# Exception: this is the CI tool that SCANS for secrets, not a secret itself.
# The broad *secret* rule above would otherwise silently exclude it from
# every commit -- caught by fixture-testing the CI setup itself.
!tools/ci/secrets_scan.py

# Exception: test-fixture JSON files legitimately describe secret-related
# test scenarios by name (e.g. sample-output-tag-only-secret.json) without
# containing any real credential -- the same *secret* rule was silently
# excluding a real, needed fixture from git-history-rewrite-planner. Real
# secret-shaped content in these files is still caught by secrets_scan.py
# scanning the actual content, not the filename.
!.claude/skills/*/test-fixtures/*.json

# Personal overrides (per-user, not shared)
CLAUDE.local.md
.claude/settings.local.json
.claude.json

# Runtime output from scheduled skills -- per-user/per-machine, not shared
.claude/skills/*/digest.log

# Python
__pycache__/
*.pyc
.venv/
venv/

# OS/editor cruft
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
*.swp
debug.log

# Generated per-runtime exports -- regenerate via tools/export-skill, never hand-edit or commit
exports/
